@SpringBootApplication
	combination of three separate annotations
		@Configuration - source of bean definitions for the application context
		@EnableAutoConfiguration - This annotation tells Spring Boot to attempt to
					automatically configure the spring application based
					on jar dependencies that are present in class path
		@ComponentScan - This annotation tells Spring Boot to scan the specified packages
				for annotated components.

@Service
	used with classes that provide business functionalities
	specialization of the @Component Annotation


@RestController
	to mark a class as a request handler. Used to create REST API
@RequestMapping("/api")
@GetMapping("/employees")
@Entity
	makes a class as entity class

@Table (name="employee")
@Id
@GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY)
@Column(name = "first_name")